    <published>2002-06-04T15:07:29Z</published>
    <title>Future Perspectives at CERN</title>
    <summary>  Current and future experiments at CERN are reviewed,with emphasis on those
relevant to astrophysics and cosmology. These include experiments related to
nuclear astrophysics, matter-antimatter asymmetry, dark matter, axions,
gravitational waves, cosmic rays, neutrino oscillations, inflation, neutron
stars and the quark-gluon plasma. The centrepiece of CERN's future programme is
the LHC, but some ideas for perspectives after the LHC are also presented.
</summary>
